
[quote]552. 新疆莎车大屠杀是否属实？[/quote]

[b]新疆莎车大屠杀是否属实？[/b]

[b]详情：[url=http://www.molihua.org/2014/09/35.html]http://www.molihua.org/2014/09/35.html[/url][/b]


[i]@维民所止：[/i]



在这里我引用一个几年前在Reddit上看到的回复（[url=https://www.reddit.com/r/China/comments/4hmhzt/xinjiang_massacre_2014_resulted_in_30005000_deaths/d2quzuq/]原文链接[/url]）：
[i]While Boxun is not the most reliable source, something huge definitely happened in Yarkent in 2014. The official account of the incident is that it was a "terrorist attack", and the official casualty count makes it most likely the largest "terrorist attack" ever to occur in China. But when Beijing talks about being a victim of terrorism, they never mention this incident.[/i]
[i]Things we do know:[/i]
[ul][li][i]The entire top leadership of the county was fired or punished after the incident, something which has not happened in other "terrorist" incidents in Xinjiang[/i][/li]
[li][i]Xinjiang Party Secretary Zhang Chunxian and Yu Zhengsheng, top Chinese official in charge of Xinjiang, personally visited the tiny village where the incident occurred multiple times, something which has not happened with other "terrorist" incidents in Xinjiang[/i][/li]
[li][i]About a year after the incident the village announced land reforms and the average land holdings per villager went up, meaning either more land was added to the village or they were given land previously owned by other people. They also abolished the corvee labor system in the village (most villages in Xinjiang are forced to perform unpaid "volunteer" labor each year)[/i][/li]
[li][i]Several foreign reporters have tried getting to the village and asking questions, but have not been able to get any answers. They do report that tensions appear very high in Yarkent still[/i][/li]
[li][i]Usually in the case of terrorist attacks an official announcement/account is quickly given, but in this case there was no official word for several days[/i][/li]
[/ul]
[i]In 2014 there were clearly many actual terrorist attacks in Xinjiang, but the official response to what happened in Yarkent was completely different from those attacks.[/i]
这个答复并没有直接描述莎车发生了什么，也没有确认莎车发生了“屠杀”。但是原文根据一些中国政府以及官媒在莎车事件前后的行为总结出2014年莎车发生了“很大的一件事”。原文要点翻译如下：
[ul][li]莎车事件后，莎车县地方大量有关领导受到党纪或行政处分（见维基百科条目：[url=https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/2014%E5%B9%B4%E8%8E%8E%E8%BD%A6%E5%8E%BF%E6%9A%B4%E6%81%90%E8%A2%AD%E5%87%BB%E6%A1%88#%E5%90%8E%E7%BB%AD%E4%BA%8B%E4%BB%B6]2014年莎车县暴恐袭击案#后续事件[/url]）。2013-2014年新疆发生的暴恐案件中，事后对党政机关人员大规模进行处罚的情况并不多见。[/li]
[li]时任新疆党委书记张春贤，以及时任中共中央政治局常委兼任中央新疆工作协调小组组长俞正声在事后亲自到莎车县视察，这也是新疆前后几年间发生的暴恐事件中罕见的行动。（天山网2014年9月8日：[url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150101105301/http://news.ts.cn/content/2014-09/08/content_10498707.htm]张春贤在莎车县考察调研[/url]，新华网2015年9月27日：[url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180916050947/http://www.xinhuanet.com/politics/2015-09/27/c_1116691205.htm]俞正声率中央代表团赴莎车县慰问考察[/url]）[/li]
[li]莎车事件发生逾一年之后，莎车县进行了“土地清理”并处理分配了“清理”出的耕地，人均耕地从2.6亩上升到3.5亩，增幅约34.6%。但当地政府并没有说明多余的耕地是新开垦的，还是已开垦但曾经属于其他个人的。（天山网2015年8月9日：[url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503174828/http://news.ts.cn/content/2015-08/09/content_11723597.htm]心系群众实际困难 提高服务群众能力[/url]）。Reddit的原帖还提到了当年莎车县居民不像新疆其他地区居民一样需要做义务工（出处见之前的天山网2014年9月8日链接），由于新疆全境已经于2017年初全面取消义务工，这一点暂且存疑。[/li]
[li]外国记者被禁止进入莎车县。但据消息称莎车县的官民关系依然相对紧张。(外国记者被噤声是当局对重大事件处理手法中的例行策略，对此亦有存疑。但当年11月莎车县确实再度发生了暴恐事件）[/li]
[li]按惯例发生暴恐事件时，当局会相对迅速地通过各种渠道发布相关通告。但莎车县暴恐事件则是在发生超过五天之后的8月2日才有政府对整个事件的细节进行官方通告。[/li]
[/ul]
原文依此得出的结论是，2014年是新疆暴恐事件的高发期，但官方对于莎车县事件的处理有别于当年在新疆发生的其它暴恐事件。所以莎车县事件的过程、性质、或是规模，可能与当年发生的其它事件有本质上的区别。


